{"word":"σκοτεινός","slug":"σκοτεινός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>σκοτεινός</b></el> <el>(σκοτεινός, ή, όν) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:σκότος'><el>σκότος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>dark</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>ἀνὰ τὸ σκοτεινόν</el> in <i>the darkness</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of a person, <i>darkling, blind</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>dark, obscure</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>:—so <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-νῶς</el>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}